===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The portion of a hammer containing the metal striking face (also including the [[claw]] or [[peen]] if so equipped).
# {{context|zoology|lang=en}} Any of various [[shark]]s of the genus ''[[Sphyrna]]'' or ''[[Zygaena]]'' having the eyes set on projections from the sides of the head, which gives it a hammer shape.
# {{context|zoology|lang=en}} A fresh-water fish; the {{vern|stone-roller}}, in the minnow family [[Cyprinidae]].
# {{context|zoology|lang=en}} An African fruit bat, the {{vern|hammer-headed fruit bat}}, {{taxlink|Hypsignathus monstrosus|species|noshow=1}}, so called from its large blunt nozzle.
# {{context|slang|lang=en}} A stupid person, a dunce.
#* '''1960:''' ''[The butler] joined us with a telegram for Bobbie on a salver. From her mother, I presumed, calling me some name which she had forgotten to insert in previous communications. Or, of course, possibly expressing once more her conviction that I was a guffin, which, I thought, having had time to ponder over it, would be something in the nature of a bohunkus or a '''hammerhead'''.'' ({{w|P. G. Wodehouse}}, ''{{w|Jeeves in the Offing}}'', chapter V)
# {{context|biology|lang=en}} A kind of [[ribozyme]]; [[hammerhead ribozyme]].

